[src:grain-language/pattern-matching] The difference then is that with variable and wildcard parts, a pattern does not build into a single value, but matches a group of values that are the combination of the concrete elements and the elements that are allowed to vary within the structure of the pattern.
[src:grain-language/pattern-matching] A tree pattern describes a part of a tree by starting with a node and specifying some branches and nodes and leaving some unspecified with a variable or wildcard pattern.
[src:grain-language/pattern-matching] It may help to think of the abstract syntax tree of a programming language and algebraic data types.
